==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tiger-eye
<hw>Ti"ger-eye`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A siliceous stone of a yellow color and chatoyant luster, obtained
in South Africa and much used for ornament. It is an altered form of the
mineral crocidolite. See <er>Crocidolite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiger-foot</ent>⟦br⟧
